    lengthMeters: 304.8,
    pitches: 15,
    fa: "FA: Joe Herbst and Larry Hamilton, Apr, 1973, FFA: Leo Henson and Dan McQuade, 1994",
    description: "The Original Route on the Rainbow Wall is perhaps Red Rocks' finest. Sustained, technical climbing, flawless rock, corner after steep corner of stems, locks, and intricate face sequences, and generally good gear lends this climb classic status. In my opinion, all of those factors, combined with the ability to climb the route with a light rack and a single rope, an incredible view, and an approach that once kept the crowds away, make this a near perfect rock climbing experience. Once and strangely still a popular aid route, the Original Route is now all-free. During the free ascent in the mid '",
